-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/spain-s-unicaja-holds-talks-to-sell-20-stake-expansion-reports.html
The newly created bank of Unicaja
and Espana-Duero is in negotiations to sell a 20 percent stake
to between three and six companies for 490 million euros ($658
million),  Expansion  reported, citing people close to the
transaction.  The new bank would need a core capital of 8 percent to pass
the next European stress test instead of the current 10.2
percent, the newspaper said. The negotiations may be already
advanced with insurers  Mapfre SA (MAP)  and  Aviva Plc (AV/) , Expansion
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
